quakes dataset

which records the location (latitude, longitude, and depth) and magnitude of several seismic events near Fiji since 1964.

data("quakes")
print(quakes)
depth.col <- grey.colors(100)[cut(quakes$depth, 100, label = FALSE)]
quakes$Magnitude <- equal.count(quakes$mag,4)
summary(quakes$Magnitude)

Intervals:

Overlap between adjacent intervals:
[1] 293 306 217

quakes$color <- depth.col
quakes.ordered <- quakes[depth.ord, ]

plot( xyplot(lat ~ long | Magnitude, data = quakes.ordered, col = "black",
       aspect = "iso", 
       fill.color = quakes.ordered$color, 
       cex = 2,
       layout = c(2,2),
       panel = function(x, y, fill.color, ..., subscripts) {
         fill <- fill.color[subscripts]
         panel.grid(h = -1, v = -1)
         panel.xyplot(x, y, pch = 21, fill = fill, ...)
       },
       xlab = "Longitude", ylab = "Latitude",
       legend = list(right = list(
         fun = draw.colorkey,
         args = list(key = list(col = grey.colors(50), at = depth.breaks),
                     draw = FALSE)
       ))
))

plot(xyplot(lat~long|cut(depth,3),data=quakes,
 layout=c(3,1),xlab="Longitude",
 ylab="Latitude"))

xyplot(lat ~ long, data = quakes, aspect = "iso",
 groups = cut(depth, breaks = quantile(depth, ppoints(4, 1))),
 auto.key = list(columns = 3, title = "Depth"),
 xlab = "Longitude", ylab = "Latitude")


depth.ord <- rev(order(quakes$depth))
xyplot(lat ~ long, data = quakes[depth.ord, ],
  aspect = "iso", type = c("p", "g"), col = "black",
  pch = 21, fill = depth.col[depth.ord], cex = 2,
  xlab = "Longitude", ylab = "Latitude")

plot(cloud(depth~lat*long|Magnitude,data=quakes,
 zlim=rev(range(quakes$depth)),
 screen=list(z=105,x=-70),panel.aspect=0.9,
 xlab="Longitude",ylab="Latitude",zlab="Depth"))

cloud(depth ~ lat * long | Magnitude, data = quakes,
 zlim = rev(range(quakes$depth)), panel.aspect = 0.9,
 screen = list(z = 80, x =-70), zoom = 0.7, 
 scales=list(z=list(arrows=FALSE,distance=2)),
 xlab="Longitude",ylab="Latitude",
 zlab=list("Depth\n(km)",rot=90))

p<-cloud(depth ~ long + lat, quakes, zlim = c(690, 30),
 pch = ".", cex = 1.5, zoom = 1,
 xlab = NULL, ylab = NULL, zlab = NULL,
 par.settings = list(axis.line = list(col = "transparent")),
 scales = list(draw = FALSE))

npanel <- 4
rotz <- seq(-30, 30, length = npanel)
roty <- c(3, 0)
update(p[rep(1, 2 * npanel)],
 layout = c(2, npanel),
 panel = function(..., screen) {
 crow <- current.row()
 ccol <- current.column()
 panel.cloud(..., screen = list(z = rotz[crow],
 x =-60,
 y = roty[ccol]))
 })

measure <- data.frame(
  chest = c(34, 37, 38, 36, 38, 43, 40, 38, 40, 41, 
            36, 36, 34, 33, 36, 37, 34, 36, 38, 35),
  waist = c(30, 32, 30, 33, 29, 32, 33, 30, 30, 32, 
            24, 25, 24, 22, 26, 26, 25, 26, 28, 23),
  hips = c(32, 37, 36, 39, 33, 38, 42, 40, 37, 39, 
           35, 37, 37, 34, 38, 37, 38, 37, 40, 35),
  gender = c("male", "male", "male", "male", "male", "male", "male", "male", "male", "male",
             "female", "female", "female", "female", "female", "female", "female", "female", "female", "female")
)

print(measure)
NA
measure$gender_numeric <- as.numeric(as.factor(measure$gender))

with(measure, scatterplot3d(chest, waist, hips,
                            pch = c(2, 1)[gender_numeric],  # Map gender to symbols
                            type = "h",
                            angle = 55))



interp_data <- with(measure, interp(x = chest, y = waist, z = hips, duplicate = "mean"))

persp(x = interp_data$x, y = interp_data$y, z = interp_data$z,
      xlab = "Chest", ylab = "Waist", zlab = "Hips",
      theta = 0, phi = 15, expand = 0.5)

      xlab = "Temperature", ylab = "Wind", zlab = "SO2",
      theta = 0, phi = 20, expand = 0.5)
